// Datasheet for the `router` device — its TYPE requirements + a storage requirement. A datasheet
// DESCRIBES REQUIREMENTS, never definitions: it states the `nodeKind` type (a device's types are its
// shared vocabulary) and that the driver must provide a `TrieNode` pool of at least 256 rows. The
// `TrieNode` SHAPE is defined in the impl (router.arche), which uses it; the driver owns the pool.
nodeKind :: enum { kstatic, kparam, kcatchall }

[256]TrieNode; // storage requirement: the driver allocates at least this many nodes